The beach was closed after a City of Cape Town employee was injured when dune collapsed during an inspection of storm damage. JOHANNESBURG – A City of Cape Town employee has been injured while inspecting storm damage on the beach in Blouberg. Mayco member for area North Suzette Little says the state of the beach at Big Bay as further deteriorated following this week's inclement weather. She says the beach has been closed off to the public indefinitely.“One of the staff members inspecting the storm damage which occurred on Tuesday and a dune then collapsed.”